{"type":"message","id":"9b759e9b","parentId":"a731b4f8","timestamp":"2026-03-22T19:59:44.207Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's no jobs or notebooks resource in the SDK. The SDK is primarily for Agents, Apps, Inference, etc. — not for managing Gradient notebooks/jobs directly.\n\nThis confirms what I suspected: the Gradient jobs/notebooks API is a separate service that isn't covered by this Python SDK. The SDK is for the newer DigitalOcean Gradient platform (agents, apps, etc.), not the legacy Paperspace Gradient notebooks.\n\nLet me tell Zach the situation clearly — the Python SDK doesn't support managing Gradient notebooks/jobs. The original job was created via the REST API (which is what the web console uses), but that API endpoint seems to not be accessible via the Python SDK.\n\nOptions:\n\n\n1. Go to paperspace.com directly and cancel the pending job from there\n2. Use Lambda Labs instead\n3. Try to call the REST API directly using curl/requests with proper authentication","thinkingSignature":"c0462107ca4c81ca019011fae2ef7cacc763e1d25e76af1d5bcde93bf8635c8d"},{"type":"text","text":"The SDK doesn't have job/notebook management — it's for Agents, Apps, and Inference. The jobs/notebooks API is a separate REST endpoint that the Python SDK doesn't wrap.\n\nEasiest path: just go to [console.paperspace.com](https://console.paperspace.com) → cancel the stuck job manually in the UI. Then we can try again or switch to Lambda.\n\nOr just tell me to spin up Lambda Labs instead — it'll be faster at this point."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":9877,"output":275,"cacheRead":12605,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22757,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774209577063}}
