{"type":"message","id":"c9eb5d3c","parentId":"26301ba2","timestamp":"2026-03-22T20:14:45.111Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the holds.md to see if there's any RTX setup code there.","thinkingSignature":"abb976c9345a371fb6bba4a17863ecbd44fb78da0e34fdfcea0bca0e370a7887"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vtx7qb3glipw_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace/holds.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":25673,"output":56,"cacheRead":12605,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38334,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774210482736}}
{"type":"message","id":"55d48be7","parentId":"c9eb5d3c","timestamp":"2026-03-22T20:14:45.127Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_vtx7qb3glipw_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Holds — Topics to Revisit Later\n\n> Use `/hold1`, `/hold2`, etc. to save topics. `/holds` to see all. `/clearhold1` to clear.\n\n## Active Holds\n\n### /hold1 — Causal-minimal project\nBuild a minimal causal reasoning system:\n- State encoder: autoencoder on frozen LLM embeddings\n- Causal layer: grid world RL env with discoverable causal graph\n- Synthesis: program synthesis on causal graph for goal-directed behavior\n- Test: does it generalize with fewer params than comparable LLM?\n- Location: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/causal-minimal/` (to be created)\n- Status: design sketched, awaiting scaffolding\n\n### /hold2 — Build our own gateway\nReplace OpenClaw's agent loop with our own lean session/context layer:\n- **Why:** Custom system prompts, full control over context injection, eliminate token overhead\n- **Current pain points:** Bootstrap files injected every turn, TOOLS.md (54KB raw), tool schemas count every turn\n- **Architecture:** Paperspace Gradient (A5000 30GB) running vLLM + fastapi → OpenClaw routes to our endpoint\n- **What we control:** Session state, context assembly, on-demand file loading, system prompt content\n- **What OpenClaw still handles:** Channel transport (Telegram, etc.)\n- **Model picked:** `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive`\n  - Qwen3.5-35B MoE (~3B active per token, 35B total)\n  - 0/465 refusals — fully uncensored\n  - Q4_K_M: 20GB VRAM — fits A5000 30GB with headroom\n  - Base: Qwen/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B (multilingual, strong reasoning)\n- **Key docs:** OpenClaw concepts/system-prompt.md, concepts/context.md, gateway/architecture.md\n- **Config knobs we found:** `agents.defaults.bootstrapTotalMaxChars`, `lightContext`, `promptMode: minimal`\n- **Status:** Model picked, awaiting Paperspace notebook setup\n\n---\n\n## Archive (cleared holds)\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774210485123}}
