{"type":"message","id":"ab43bfbb","parentId":"01206dc3","timestamp":"2026-03-22T20:34:41.844Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants me to scaffold the CodeCause project. Let me create the project structure and start building. I'll:\n\n1. Create the project directory structure\n2. Write the architecture document\n3. Start with the causal graph indexer as the first component\n4. Write a spec\n\nLet me think about the structure:\n\n```\nC:/dev/code-cause/\n  SPEC.md\n  README.md\n  src/\n    causal_indexer/       # First pass: builds causal graph from code\n    world_model/          # VAE latent space\n    dual_head/            # Training loop from infant\n    temporal_attention/   # Focus decay\n    agent/                # Planning loop\n    codegen/              # Small decoder model\n  experiments/\n  tests/\n  scripts/\n```\n\nThe first and most concrete thing is the **causal graph indexer**. This takes a codebase and builds a dependency graph. It answers questions like \"if I change function X, what breaks?\"\n\n\nI'll tackle this first since it gives us immediate utility—we can surface it through component-crate or a CLI tool—while the research on world models and dual-head architectures continues. Let me start building out the directory structure and core modules.","thinkingSignature":"2d1f3befdb5ca74342736f7d48992b4cb33e31c1132fa11b47bc41d35b243930"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wj0x2gbcr8kr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path \"C:\\dev\\code-cause\\src\\causal_indexer\" 2>&1 && New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path \"C:\\dev\\code-cause\\src\\world_model\" 2>&1 && New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path \"C:\\dev\\code-cause\\src\\dual_head\" 2>&1 && New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path \"C:\\dev\\code-cause\\src\\temporal_attention\" 2>&1 && New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path \"C:\\dev\\code-cause\\src\\agent\" 2>&1 && New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path \"C:\\dev\\code-cause\\src\\codegen\" 2>&1 && New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path \"C:\\dev\\code-cause\\experiments\" 2>&1 && New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path \"C:\\dev\\code-cause\\tests\" 2>&1 && New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path \"C:\\dev\\code-cause\\scripts\" 2>&1 && New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path \"C:\\dev\\code-cause\\data\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":541,"cacheRead":1307,"cacheWrite":42205,"totalTokens":44096,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774211667436}}
{"type":"message","id":"f7123b5c","parentId":"ab43bfbb","timestamp":"2026-03-22T20:34:43.176Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wj0x2gbcr8kr_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Directory: C:\\dev\\code-cause\\src\r\n\r\n[32;1mMode   [0m[32;1m              LastWriteTime[0m [32;1;3m        Length[0m[32;1m Name[0m\r\n[32;1m----   [0m [32;1m             -------------[0m [32;1m        ------[0m [32;1m----[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mcausal_indexer[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mworld_model[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mdual_head[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mtemporal_attention[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1magent[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mcodegen[0m\r\n\r\n    Directory: C:\\dev\\code-cause\r\n\r\n[32;1mMode   [0m[32;1m              LastWriteTime[0m [32;1;3m        Length[0m[32;1m Name[0m\r\n[32;1m----   [0m [32;1m             -------------[0m [32;1m        ------[0m [32;1m----[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mexperiments[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mtests[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mscripts[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mdata[0m"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1312,"aggregated":"Directory: C:\\dev\\code-cause\\src\r\n\r\n[32;1mMode   [0m[32;1m              LastWriteTime[0m [32;1;3m        Length[0m[32;1m Name[0m\r\n[32;1m----   [0m [32;1m             -------------[0m [32;1m        ------[0m [32;1m----[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mcausal_indexer[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mworld_model[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mdual_head[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mtemporal_attention[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1magent[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mcodegen[0m\r\n\r\n    Directory: C:\\dev\\code-cause\r\n\r\n[32;1mMode   [0m[32;1m              LastWriteTime[0m [32;1;3m        Length[0m[32;1m Name[0m\r\n[32;1m----   [0m [32;1m             -------------[0m [32;1m        ------[0m [32;1m----[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mexperiments[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mtests[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mscripts[0m\r\nd----           3/22/2026  4:34 PM                [44;1mdata[0m","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774211683168}}
{"type":"message","id":"a9395714","parentId":"f7123b5c","timestamp":"2026-03-22T20:35:17.243Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me write the SPEC.md and the core files. I'll start with the spec, then the causal indexer (the first concrete component), and a minimal working demo.","thinkingSignature":"0584643c2343fcf0bff9b9d4147829a3e74e4a60821038d4374b7f2ccd64ce9a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1cht5mnrubku_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:/dev/code-cause/SPEC.md","content":"# CodeCause — SPEC.md\n\n## 1. Concept & Vision\n\nCodeCause is a causal reasoning coding agent — not a better text generator, but a fundamentally different kind of intelligence applied to code. It builds a persistent causal model of a codebase: understanding *what* code does and *what it affects*, not just what tokens tend to follow other tokens.\n\nThe goal is an agent that can reason about a 50k-line codebase in ways GPT-5 literally cannot — because it has genuine causal structure, not just statistical patterns learned from next-token prediction.\n\n**The bet:** Causal reasoning over code structure beats scale. You don't need a 405B model to understand a codebase — you need the right representation.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Architecture Overview\n\n```\nCodebase → Frozen Backbone → Causal World Model\n              ↓                    ↓\n        [Token Embeddings]   [Disentangled Latent Z]\n                                     ↓\n                           [Causal Dependency Graph]\n                                     ↓\n                           [Dual-Head Architecture]\n                           /                    \\\n                    [Slow Head]             [Fast Head]\n                  (persistent world)      (current task)\n                           \\                    /\n                        [Agent Planner]\n                                ↓\n                    [Action: Query / Generate / Update]\n                                ↓\n                      [Verified Code Output]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Four Core Subsystems\n\n### 3.1 Causal World Model (`world_model/`)\n**From:** COG-research VAE experiments  \n**Role:** Learns disentangled latent space of code — functional meaning, not token patterns.\n\nTraining signal: execution traces. When code runs, the world model learns which latent variables correspond to which runtime behaviors. Contrastive learning on (code → execution outcome) pairs.\n\n**Output:** `z ∈ R^d` — a vector representation where different dimensions correspond to independent aspects of code behavior. Plus an adjacency matrix over the causal graph.\n\n**Status:** Design exists in COG-research. Needs extraction and adaptation.\n\n### 3.2 Dual-Head Architecture (`dual_head/`)\n**From:** infant project (dual-head prevents catastrophic forgetting)  \n**Role:** Persistent memory without interference.\n\n- **Slow head:** Global world model of the codebase. Updated via exponential moving average. Never overwritten by new tasks — only refined.\n- **Fast head:** Task-specific adapter. Resets between tasks. Learns the current context quickly.\n\nWhen switching tasks: fast head resets, slow head persists. The agent \"remembers\" the codebase structure even when starting a new task.\n\n**Status:** Fully implemented in infant. Needs integration.\n\n### 3.3 Temporal Attention (`temporal_attention/`)\n**From:** temporal-attention project (focus decay)  \n**Role:** Determines *what to attend to* from the causal graph for any given query.\n\nKey mechanism: attention weights decay based on recency and relevance. Long-horizon dependencies (critical function that everything calls) stay high priority. Recent changes decay but don't disappear entirely.\n\n**Output:** Given a query, returns the subgraph of the causal model most relevant to it.\n\n**Status:** Implemented in temporal-attention. Needs integration.\n\n### 3.4 Causal Graph Indexer (`causal_indexer/`) ⚡ FIRST PROTOTYPE\n**Role:** Static analysis + dynamic tracing to build the causal dependency graph.\n\nStatic: AST parsing to extract import/call/extend/override relationships.  \nDynamic: Runtime instrumentation to capture actual call paths (opt-in, with a flag).\n\nThis is the first concrete deliverable — a usable tool that works WITHOUT the world model. It indexes a codebase and builds a queryable dependency graph.\n\n### 3.5 Agent Planner (`agent/`)\n**From:** selfhelper-main (autonomous planning + tool use)  \n**Role:** Given a task, plans a sequence of interventions in causal space.\n\n1. Query causal graph: \"what does this change affect?\"\n2. Plan in latent space: identify the minimal set of changes needed\n3. Execute: call codegen with the right context\n4. Verify: execution trace → update world model\n\n### 3.6 Code Generator (`codegen/`)\nSmall decoder model (CodeLlama or Qwen variant, 1-7B params) fine-tuned to take causal-conditioned prompts. Not a frontier model — it's a specialist that responds to the world model's queries.\n\n**Note:** v1 may use an external LLM API as the codegen while the causal layer is developed.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Component Status\n\n| Component | Status | Notes |\n|-----------|--------|-------|\n| `causal_indexer` | 🔴 Building now | Static AST + dynamic tracing |\n| `world_model` | 🟡 Designed | VAE from COG-research needs extraction |\n| `dual_head` | ✅ Available | infant project, needs integration |\n| `temporal_attention` | ✅ Available | temporal-attention, needs integration |\n| `agent` | 🟡 Designed | selfhelper-main patterns |\n| `codegen` | 🔵 External v1 | Use API while causal layer matures |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Why This Is Novel\n\n**Current LLMs:** Statistical pattern matching over token sequences. Context-limited. No verification. Forgets between sessions.\n\n**CodeCause:** Causal reasoning over code structure. Persistent codebase model. Predicts effects before generation. Remembers across sessions.\n\n**The key insight:** Code is fundamentally causal — every function call has a defined effect, every dependency is a causal edge. LLMs are trained to predict text; they don't learn the causal structure of programs, they learn the statistical regularities of how humans write programs. These are different things.\n\nThe causal world model is what makes it possible to generalize to novel codebases and novel tasks without retraining.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Product Path (Component Crate Integration)\n\nCodeCause's causal graph indexer is the immediate deliverable for component-crate:\n\n1. **Free tier:** Static dependency graph (imports, calls, extends)\n2. **Premium tier:** Dynamic tracing + causal ranking of changes + slow-head persistence across sessions\n\nThe full CodeCause architecture (world model + dual head + agent) is the research moonshot that makes component-crate defensible long-term.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Files\n\n```\ncode-cause/\n  SPEC.md                    # This file\n  README.md                  # Overview + quick start\n  src/\n    causal_indexer/          # Causal dependency graph builder\n      __init__.py\n      static_analyzer.py     # AST-based static analysis\n      dynamic_tracer.py      # Runtime instrumentation (opt-in)\n      graph_builder.py       # Build causal adjacency from analysis\n      query_engine.py        # Query the graph (what affects X?)\n    world_model/             # VAE latent space (COG-research port)\n    dual_head/               # Dual-head training (from infant)\n    temporal_attention/      # Focus decay (from temporal-attention)\n    agent/                   # Planning loop (from selfhelper-main)\n    codegen/                 # Small decoder specialist\n  experiments/               # Evaluation benchmarks\n  tests/                     # Unit + integration tests\n  scripts/                   # CLI tools\n  data/                      # Cached graphs\n```\n\n---\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-22 — Scaffolded by Nova ✨_\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":31972,"output":1571,"cacheRead":12605,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46148,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774211683181}}
