{"type":"message","id":"f0194c6a","parentId":"f4ad4f75","timestamp":"2026-03-22T20:35:24.345Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me write the causal indexer. This is the first concrete component. I'll build:\n\n1. `static_analyzer.py` - AST-based analysis of Python/JS/TS codebases\n2. `graph_builder.py` - Builds the causal graph from analysis\n3. `query_engine.py` - Queries the graph\n4. `__init__.py` - Clean API\n\nLet me start with the static analyzer, then the graph builder, then the query engine.","thinkingSignature":"1065c7e8ab6d22a8af5097151f168c4697b67c1cfded8b898f9b424db6ec09dc"},{"type":"text","text":"Now the causal indexer — the first concrete component:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i9o1l8hu13da_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:/dev/code-cause/src/causal_indexer/__init__.py","content":"\"\"\"\nCodeCause Causal Indexer\n========================\nBuilds a causal dependency graph from a codebase via static analysis.\nDynamic tracing available as an opt-in enhancement.\n\nUsage:\n    from causal_indexer import CodebaseGraph\n\n    graph = CodebaseGraph()\n    graph.index(\"path/to/codebase\")\n    graph.save(\"graph.json\")\n\n    # Query: what would break if I change function X?\n    effects = graph.query_impact(\"my_module.my_function\")\n    # Query: what caused the bug in function Y?\n    causes = graph.query_causes(\"my_module.buggy_function\")\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom .static_analyzer import StaticAnalyzer\nfrom .graph_builder import CausalGraph\nfrom .query_engine import QueryEngine\n\n__all__ = [\"StaticAnalyzer\", \"CausalGraph\", \"QueryEngine\"]\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":33574,"output":320,"cacheRead":12605,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46499,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774211717278}}
