{"type":"message","id":"12e7a36c","parentId":"7e92b224","timestamp":"2026-03-22T20:38:05.426Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me write the README and then a simple test. Then update memory.","thinkingSignature":"941cdbf654dc68979cfc67c0a63051dbf8dc32eb8193e8035c0b7f7b30ddd022"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cyi5puqcdh3w_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:/dev/code-cause/README.md","content":"# CodeCause ✨\n\n**Causal coding agent** — not a better text generator, but a fundamentally different kind of intelligence applied to code.\n\nCodeCause builds a persistent causal model of a codebase: understanding *what* code does and *what it affects*. It reasons about code the way a human expert does — in terms of dependencies, side effects, and causal chains — not in terms of next-token probabilities.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n```bash\n# Index any codebase\npython scripts/index_codebase.py /path/to/your/codebase\n\n# Query what changes if you modify a function\npython scripts/index_codebase.py /path/to/your/codebase \\\n  --query \"what happens if I change auth.validate_token?\"\n\n# Query what caused a bug\npython scripts/index_codebase.py /path/to/your/codebase \\\n  --query \"what caused errors in processor.run_batch?\"\n```\n\n## What It Does\n\n1. **Static Analysis** — Parses Python and JavaScript/TypeScript to extract definitions, calls, imports, and inheritance\n2. **Causal Graph** — Builds a directed dependency graph from the analysis\n3. **Causal Queries** — Answers questions like \"what breaks if I change X?\" or \"what does X depend on?\"\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\ncode-cause/\n  src/\n    causal_indexer/       # Graph building from static analysis\n    world_model/          # VAE latent space (future)\n    dual_head/            # Persistent memory (future)\n    temporal_attention/   # Focus decay (future)\n    agent/               # Planning loop (future)\n  experiments/\n  tests/\n  scripts/\n```\n\n## The Full Vision\n\nThe causal graph indexer is the first concrete deliverable. The full CodeCause architecture adds:\n\n- **World Model**: VAE latent space for functional code understanding\n- **Dual-Head Memory**: Slow head (persistent codebase model) + Fast head (current task)\n- **Temporal Attention**: Focus decay for long-horizon queries\n- **Agent Planner**: Plans interventions in causal space\n\nThe full system is what makes component-crate premium tier defensible — a coding assistant that *understands* your codebase in a way no current LLM can.\n\n## Status\n\n| Component | Status |\n|-----------|--------|\n| Causal Graph Indexer | ✅ Working |\n| Python Analysis | ✅ Working |\n| JS/TS Analysis | ✅ Basic (regex fallback) |\n| Query Engine | ✅ Working |\n| World Model | 🔬 Research |\n| Dual-Head Memory | 🔬 Research |\n| Temporal Attention | 🔬 Research |\n\n---\n\n_Built 2026-03-22 by Nova ✨ as the first concrete step toward a genuinely new kind of coding intelligence._\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43197,"output":612,"cacheRead":12605,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56414,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774211870207}}
