{"type":"message","id":"9082c28a","parentId":"e4835b49","timestamp":"2026-03-22T20:41:11.495Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so:\n1. Entity is extracted correctly: `EventBasedStore._apply_focus_decay`\n2. It resolves to `.EventBasedStore._apply_focus_decay` (the leading dot is the module prefix)\n3. But `query_impact` returns 0 impacts\n\nThe issue is that `_apply_focus_decay` is a method that doesn't call any OTHER defined entities - it probably only calls built-in Python functions or external library functions. So the static analyzer sees no outgoing edges from it.\n\nLet me find an entity that DOES have outgoing edges.","thinkingSignature":"25f6cc097e8dcfe339b1d2e9737cff77f3b689194c9d96a75f80af9f4a0d033b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hwqz6w8b45vg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"C:/Users/Zwmar/AppData/Local/Programs/Python/Python312/python.exe -c \"\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, 'C:/dev/code-cause/src')\nfrom causal_indexer import StaticAnalyzer, CausalGraph\n\nanalyzer = StaticAnalyzer('C:/dev/temporal-attention')\nanalyzer.analyze()\ngraph = CausalGraph.from_analysis(analyzer.definitions, analyzer.references)\n\n# Find entities with outgoing edges to OTHER defined entities (not external)\noutgoing_to_internal = []\nfor en, outs in graph._outgoing.items():\n    internal_targets = [o for o in outs if o in graph.nodes and graph.nodes[o].kind != 'external']\n    if internal_targets:\n        outgoing_to_internal.append((en, internal_targets[:3]))\n\nprint(f'Entities with internal outgoing edges: {len(outgoing_to_internal)}')\nfor en, targets in outgoing_to_internal[:10]:\n    print(f'  {en} -> {targets}')\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":52480,"output":345,"cacheRead":12605,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65430,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774212063401}}
