{"type":"message","id":"06f7865b","parentId":"3c010b70","timestamp":"2026-03-22T20:42:25.532Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `BlockManager` would be in `kv_evict/core/block_manager.py` as `kv_evict.core.BlockManager`. But the reference says `kv_evict.BlockManager` (without `.core`).\n\nThis is because the import in Python was `from kv_evict import BlockManager` which means `BlockManager` is exported from `kv_evict/__init__.py` or directly from the `kv_evict` package namespace. The static analyzer correctly records the reference as `kv_evict.BlockManager`.\n\nThe issue is that the graph has:\n- Node: `apps.kv-eviction-optimizer.kv_evict.core.BlockManager` (the actual definition)  \n\n\n- Reference: `kv_evict.BlockManager` (the as-written import)\n\nThese don't match! The path normalization is the culprit—directories with hyphens get converted to modules with underscores in Python, so `apps/kv-eviction-optimizer/kv_evict/core/block_manager.py` becomes `apps.kv_eviction_optimizer.kv_evict.core.BlockManager`, but the import reference doesn't account for this conversion.\n\nThe analyzer computes module names by joining directory parts with dots and stripping the file extension, but it's not converting hyphens to underscores in the process. I need to fix the analyzer to normalize paths the same way Python actually resolves imports.","thinkingSignature":"1c55769a78ee63d868f80cd296ee184f80b47ec4b09706a595ccf01563f1b4b4"},{"type":"text","text":"Found the bug — the analyzer isn't converting `hyphenated-directory-names` → `hyphenated_directory_names` (Python package convention). Let me fix it:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1y1a19trlty4_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/dev/code-cause/src/causal_indexer/static_analyzer.py","offset":50,"limit":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":56620,"output":361,"cacheRead":12605,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69586,"