{"type":"message","id":"1ef23363","parentId":"f1b05633","timestamp":"2026-03-22T20:42:50.929Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also fix the graph builder to try resolving references to modules with hyphens → underscores conversion. The issue is that when we see `from kv_evict import BlockManager` and the kv_evict package is inside a hyphenated directory, the reference target `kv_evict.BlockManager` won't match the node `apps.kv_eviction_optimizer.kv_evict.BlockManager` or `apps.kv_eviction_optimizer.kv_evict.core.BlockManager`.\n\nActually, the problem is simpler. When we see `from kv_evict import BlockManager`, we record the reference as:\n- source_qualified: `apps.kv_eviction_optimizer.examples.main` (with underscore for hyphenated parent dir)\n\n\n- target_qualified: `kv_evict.BlockManager`\n\nBut there's no node with qualified name `kv_evict.BlockManager`. The actual node name is `apps.kv_eviction_optimizer.kv_evict.core.BlockManager`. The real issue is that Python's import system resolves `kv_evict` to the `kv_evict/` directory through the PYTHONPATH, but we're computing qualified names relative to the analysis root, so these two naming conventions don't align. I should resolve the reference target by looking up the actual module path in sys.modules or by checking where `kv_evict` actually resolves to in the file system.\n\nActually, the simplest approach is to just record the raw import statement as-is in the reference and let the graph builder handle matching by checking if a reference target matches the suffix of any node name. Though that could create false positives with common names like `utils`. A better strategy is to build a mapping from simple module names to their full paths by scanning the indexed definitions, so when we encounter `kv_evict.BlockManager`, we can look it up directly in that map rather than trying to construct the path ourselves.","thinkingSignature":"8415109e7f15fe611bdfc4cb305a7e53ba6ee8172ed4f0f9697ee270c0a8f234"},{"type":"text","text":"Also need to fix reference resolution in the graph builder — `kv_evict.BlockManager` needs to map to the actual node even though the directory is `kv-eviction-optimizer`:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5et8bpjnmwxc_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/dev/code-cause/src/causal_indexer/graph_builder.py","offset":60,"limit":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58004,"output":474,"cacheRead":12605,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71083,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774212159701}}
